Approved For Release 2011/02/23: CIA-RDP88-00434R000400640001-2 Directorate of Intelligence TV cDirectory of Chinese Officials: Provincial Organizations C A Reference Aid O ~ CR 86-11054 Oo (Supersedes CR 84-15/74) March 1986 Approved For Release 2011/02/23: CIA-RDP88-00434R000400640001-2 Approved For Release 2011/02/23: CIA-RDP88-00434R000400640001-2 Directorate of Intelligence Directory of Chinese Officials: Provincial Organizations Information available as of 10 March 1986 was used in the preparation of this publication. CR 86-11054 (Supersedes CR 84-15174) March 1986 Approved For Release 2011/02/23: CIA-RDP88-00434R000400640001-2 Approved For Release 2011/02/23: CIA-RDP88-00434R000400640001-2 The Directory of Chinese Officials. Provincial Organizations identifies individuals who hold positions on the provincial level in the Chinese Commu- nist Party (CCP), legislatures, governments, and selected mass organizations. It also identifies those who hold posts in military regions and military district headquarters and in the CCP and government organizations of the provincial capitals. The early and late dates denote specific identification of an individual in his position. Early dates are current up to 10 March 1986; late dates are current up to 31 January 1986. The names of members and alternate members of the Central Committtee of the CCP are followed by Mbr, CC, and Alt Mbr, CC, respectively. Members of the Central Advisory Commission are denoted by Mbr, CAC. The names of females are followed by the letter f. The directory may be used to find both the incumbents in given positions within an organization and the positions of specific individuals. Also included are an organization index and an alphabetical index of personalities, with Standard Telegraphic Codes when available. The orthography adopted is the Pinyin system for the romanization of Chinese characters. When romanized versions of Uygur, Zang and other minority names are known, they are used: otherwise the Chinese phonetics of those names are rendered in Pinyin. This reference aid supersedes CR 84-15174 dated October 1984. Other volumes in the Directory of Chinese Officials series are National Level Organizations (CR 85-12068) and Scientific and Educational Organizations (CR 85-10229). In the future these volumes will be combined into one Directory of Chinese Officials.
